verses.text: Also I in the first year of Darius the Mede , \add even\add* I, stood to confirm and to strengthen him.

And now will I shew thee the truth. Behold, there shall stand up yet three kings in Persia ; and the fourth shall be far richer than \add they\add* all : and by his strength through his riches he shall stir up all against the realm of Grecia.
And a mighty king shall stand up , that shall rule with great dominion , and do according to his will.

And when he shall stand up , his kingdom shall be broken , and shall be divided toward the four winds of heaven ; and not to his posterity , nor according to his dominion which he ruled : for his kingdom shall be plucked up , even for others beside those. \p
¶ And the king of the south shall be strong , and \add one\add* of his princes ; and he shall be strong above him, and have dominion ; his dominion \add shall be\add* a great dominion.

And in the end of years they shall join themselves together ; for the king’s daughter of the south shall come to the king of the north to make an agreement : but she shall not retain the power of the arm ; neither shall he stand , nor his arm : but she shall be given up , and they that brought her, and he that begat her, and he that strengthened her in \add these\add* times.\f + \fr 11.6 \ft join…: Heb. associate themselves\f*\f + \fr 11.6 \ft an…: Heb. rights\f*\f + \fr 11.6 \ft he that begat…: or, whom she brought forth\f*

But out of a branch of her roots shall \add one\add* stand up in his estate , which shall come with an army , and shall enter into the fortress of the king of the north , and shall deal against them, and shall prevail :\f + \fr 11.7 \ft in…: or, in his place, or, office\f*

And shall also carry captives into Egypt their gods , with their princes , \add and\add* with their precious vessels of silver and of gold ; and he shall continue \add more\add* years than the king of the north.\f + \fr 11.8 \ft their precious…: Heb. vessels of their desire\f*
So the king of the south shall come into \add his\add* kingdom , and shall return into his own land.

But his sons shall be stirred up , and shall assemble a multitude of great forces : and \add one\add* shall certainly come , and overflow , and pass through : then shall he return , and be stirred up , \add even\add* to his fortress.\f + \fr 11.10 \ft shall be…: or, shall war\f*\f + \fr 11.10 \ft return…: or, be stirred up again\f*

And the king of the south shall be moved with choler , and shall come forth and fight with him, \add even\add* with the king of the north : and he shall set forth a great multitude ; but the multitude shall be given into his hand.
\add And\add* when he hath taken away the multitude , his heart shall be lifted up ; and he shall cast down \add many\add* ten thousands : but he shall not be strengthened \add by it\add*.

For the king of the north shall return , and shall set forth a multitude greater than the former , and shall certainly come after certain years with a great army and with much riches.\f + \fr 11.13 \ft after…: Heb. at the end of times, even years\f*

And in those times there shall many stand up against the king of the south : also the robbers of thy people shall exalt themselves to establish the vision ; but they shall fall.\f + \fr 11.14 \ft the robbers: Heb. the children of robbers\f*

So the king of the north shall come , and cast up a mount , and take the most fenced cities : and the arms of the south shall not withstand , neither his chosen people , neither \add shall there be any\add* strength to withstand.\f + \fr 11.15 \ft the most…: Heb. the city of munitions\f*\f + \fr 11.15 \ft his…: Heb. the people of his choices\f*

But he that cometh against him shall do according to his own will , and none shall stand before him: and he shall stand in the glorious land , which by his hand shall be consumed.\f + \fr 11.16 \ft glorious…: or, goodly, etc.: Heb. land of ornament\f*

He shall also set his face to enter with the strength of his whole kingdom , and upright ones with him; thus shall he do : and he shall give him the daughter of women , corrupting her: but she shall not stand \add on his side\add*, neither be for him.\f + \fr 11.17 \ft upright…: or, much uprightness: or, equal conditions\f*\f + \fr 11.17 \ft corrupting: Heb. to corrupt\f*

After this shall he turn his face unto the isles , and shall take many : but a prince for his own behalf shall cause the reproach offered by him to cease ; without his own reproach he shall cause \add it\add* to turn upon him.\f + \fr 11.18 \ft for…: Heb. for him\f*\f + \fr 11.18 \ft the reproach…: Heb. his reproach\f*
Then he shall turn his face toward the fort of his own land : but he shall stumble and fall , and not be found.

Then shall stand up in his estate a raiser of taxes \add in\add* the glory of the kingdom : but within few days he shall be destroyed , neither in anger , nor in battle.\f + \fr 11.20 \ft estate: or, place\f*\f + \fr 11.20 \ft a…: Heb. one that causeth an exacter to pass over\f*\f + \fr 11.20 \ft anger: Heb. angers\f* \p

And in his estate shall stand up a vile person , to whom they shall not give the honour of the kingdom : but he shall come in peaceably , and obtain the kingdom by flatteries.\f + \fr 11.21 \ft estate: or, place\f*
And with the arms of a flood shall they be overflown from before him, and shall be broken ; yea, also the prince of the covenant.
And after the league \add made\add* with him he shall work deceitfully : for he shall come up , and shall become strong with a small people.

He shall enter peaceably even upon the fattest places of the province ; and he shall do \add that\add* which his fathers have not done , nor his fathers’ fathers ; he shall scatter among them the prey , and spoil , and riches : \add yea\add*, and he shall forecast his devices against the strong holds , even for a time.\f + \fr 11.24 \ft peaceably…: or, into the peaceable and fat, etc\f*\f + \fr 11.24 \ft forecast…: Heb. think his thoughts\f*

And he shall stir up his power and his courage against the king of the south with a great army ; and the king of the south shall be stirred up to battle with a very great and mighty army ; but he shall not stand : for they shall forecast devices against him.
Yea, they that feed of the portion of his meat shall destroy him, and his army shall overflow : and many shall fall down slain.

And both these kings’ hearts \add shall be\add* to do mischief , and they shall speak lies at one table ; but it shall not prosper : for yet the end \add shall be\add* at the time appointed.\f + \fr 11.27 \ft hearts: Heb. their hearts\f*
Then shall he return into his land with great riches ; and his heart \add shall be\add* against the holy covenant ; and he shall do \add exploits\add*, and return to his own land.
At the time appointed he shall return , and come toward the south ; but it shall not be as the former , or as the latter. \p

¶ For the ships of Chittim shall come against him: therefore he shall be grieved , and return , and have indignation against the holy covenant : so shall he do ; he shall even return , and have intelligence with them that forsake the holy covenant.

And arms shall stand on his part, and they shall pollute the sanctuary of strength , and shall take away the daily \add sacrifice\add*, and they shall place the abomination that maketh desolate.\f + \fr 11.31 \ft maketh…: or, astonisheth\f*

And such as do wickedly against the covenant shall he corrupt by flatteries : but the people that do know their God shall be strong , and do \add exploits\add*.\f + \fr 11.32 \ft corrupt: or, cause to dissemble\f*
And they that understand among the people shall instruct many : yet they shall fall by the sword , and by flame , by captivity , and by spoil , \add many\add* days.
Now when they shall fall , they shall be holpen with a little help : but many shall cleave to them with flatteries.

And \add some\add* of them of understanding shall fall , to try them, and to purge , and to make \add them\add* white , \add even\add* to the time of the end : because \add it is\add* yet for a time appointed.\f + \fr 11.35 \ft try them: or, try by them\f*

And the king shall do according to his will ; and he shall exalt himself, and magnify himself above every god , and shall speak marvellous things against the God of gods , and shall prosper till the indignation be accomplished : for that that is determined shall be done.
Neither shall he regard the God of his fathers , nor the desire of women , nor regard any god : for he shall magnify himself above all.

But in his estate shall he honour the God of forces : and a god whom his fathers knew not shall he honour with gold , and silver , and with precious stones , and pleasant things.\f + \fr 11.38 \ft in…: or, as for the Almighty God, in his seat he shall honour yea, he shall honour a god, whom, etc\f*\f + \fr 11.38 \ft estate: or, stead\f*\f + \fr 11.38 \ft forces: or, munitions: Heb. Mauzzim, or, God’s protectors\f*\f + \fr 11.38 \ft pleasant: Heb. things desired\f*

Thus shall he do in the most strong holds with a strange god , whom he shall acknowledge \add and\add* increase with glory : and he shall cause them to rule over many , and shall divide the land for gain.\f + \fr 11.39 \ft most…: Heb. fortresses of munitions\f*\f + \fr 11.39 \ft gain: Heb. a price\f*

And at the time of the end shall the king of the south push at him: and the king of the north shall come against him like a whirlwind , with chariots , and with horsemen , and with many ships ; and he shall enter into the countries , and shall overflow and pass over.

He shall enter also into the glorious land , and many \add countries\add* shall be overthrown : but these shall escape out of his hand , \add even\add* Edom , and Moab , and the chief of the children of Ammon.\f + \fr 11.41 \ft glorious…: or, goodly, etc.: Heb. land of delight, or, ornament\f*
He shall stretch forth his hand also upon the countries : and the land of Egypt shall not escape.\f + \fr 11.42 \ft stretch…: Heb. send forth\f*
But he shall have power over the treasures of gold and of silver , and over all the precious things of Egypt : and the Libyans and the Ethiopians \add shall be\add* at his steps.
But tidings out of the east and out of the north shall trouble him: therefore he shall go forth with great fury to destroy , and utterly to make away many.

And he shall plant the tabernacles of his palace between the seas in the glorious holy mountain ; yet he shall come to his end , and none shall help him.\f + \fr 11.45 \ft glorious…: or, goodly, etc.: Heb. mountain of delight of holiness\f*
